'''Christopher Muncke''' (d. [[April 6]], [[2022]])<ref name="Death" /> was an American actor who played [[Captain]] [[Edmos Khurgee]], the scanning crew leader and [[pilot]], in [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']].

Muncke retired from acting in 1990, transitioning to a career as a schoolteacher. In an interview, he said that his only contact in the film industry after his retirement was "when I am fortunate enough to be invited to events where I can meet and chat with Fans whether they are part of what I like to call our ''Star Wars'' Fan Family."<ref name="Interview">{{WebCite|url=https://starwarsinterviews.com/original-trilogy/episode-iv-a-new-hope/chris-muncke-captain-khurgee|text=Chris Muncke (Captain Khurgee)|author=[[Dennis Pellegrom]]|date=2011-05|work=[[Star Wars Interviews]]|archivedate=20230205201645|nolive=1}}</ref>

Muncke passed away on April 6, 2022 at the age of 79.<ref name="Death" />

